==English==

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: jôr
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /ʤɔː/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /dZO:/

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# One of the bones, usually bearing teeth, which form the framework of the mouth.
# The bone itself with the teeth and covering.
# (''figurative'') Anything resembling the jaw of an animal in form or action; especially plural, the mouth or way of entrance; as, the jaws of a pass; the jaws of darkness; the jaws of death.
# A notch or opening.
# A notched or forked part, adapted for holding an object in place; as, the jaw of a railway-car pedestal. See Axle guard.
# One of a pair of opposing parts which are movable towards or from each other, for grasping or crushing anything between them, as, the jaws of a vise, or the jaws of a stone-crushing machine.
# The inner end of a boom or gaff, hollowed in a half circle so as to move freely on a mast.
# Impudent or abusive talk.
# {{slang}} [[Axle guard]].

